article.headline: Pepperdine 93, N. Arizona 87
article.story: FLAGSTAFF, Ariz. (AP) -- Mychel Thompson scored six of his 22 points in overtime as Pepperdine beat Northern Arizona 93-87 Wednesday night. Jason Walberg also scored 22 points for the Waves (3-4) while Tyrone Shelley bounced back from a two-point first half to finish with 19 points and nine rebounds. Kyle Landry led Northern Arizona (3-3) with 17 points and 13 rebounds. Matt Johnson finished with 14 points and Nate Geiser had 13 for the Lumberjacks. Pepperdine trailed by 13 points with 4:46 left in the first half and were down 52-44 at halftime. Shelley's 3-pointer with four seconds remaining sent the game into overtime.
